{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-18",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_18_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "The Fall Guy",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 5,
  "page_total": 8,
  "page_start_sec": 988.58,
  "page_end_sec": 1231.1,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.553,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 988.58,
      "end": 989.22,
      "text": "You make"
    },
    {
      "start": 989.28,
      "end": 990.3,
      "text": "me decidedly uncomfortable."
    },
    {
      "start": 990.88,
      "end": 992.72,
      "text": "I shouldn't have laughed,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 993.14,
      "end": 995.0,
      "text": "and I apologize most humbly and sincerely."
    },
    {
      "start": 995.68,
      "end": 999.22,
      "text": "I wouldn't want to seem to ridicule anything you'd suggest,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 999.38,
      "end": 999.54,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 999.6,
      "end": 999.94,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1000.12,
      "end": 1002.5,
      "text": "regardless of how much I disagreed with you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1002.6,
      "end": 1004.7,
      "text": "for you must know that I have the greatest"
    },
    {
      "start": 1004.7,
      "end": 1007.42,
      "text": "respect and admiration for your astuteness."
    },
    {
      "start": 1007.54,
      "end": 1007.648,
      "text": "Now,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1008.42,
      "end": 1008.9,
      "text": "mind you,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1009.22,
      "end": 1012.66,
      "text": "I don't see how the suggestion of yours can be in any way practical,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1013.36,
      "end": 1015.64,
      "text": "even leaving out the fact that I couldn't feel",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1015.64,
      "end": 1018.16,
      "text": "any different towards Wilmer if he was my own"
    },
    {
      "start": 1018.2,
      "end": 1018.82,
      "text": "flesh and blood,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1019.46,
      "end": 1021.54,
      "text": "but I'll consider it a personal favor as",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1021.54,
      "end": 1023.88,
      "text": "well as a sign that you've accepted my"
    },
    {
      "start": 1023.98,
      "end": 1024.44,
      "text": "apologies,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1024.64,
      "end": 1024.86,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1025.42,
      "end": 1027.44,
      "text": "if you'll go ahead and outline the rest of it.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1028.18,
      "end": 1028.54,
      "text": "Fair enough,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1028.76,
      "end": 1029.48,
      "text": "Spade said."
    },
    {
      "start": 1029.72,
      "end": 1030.27,
      "text": "Brian"
    },
    {
      "start": 1030.66,
      "end": 1032.18,
      "text": "is like most district attorneys."
    },
    {
      "start": 1032.57,
      "end": 1035.46,
      "text": "He's more interested in how his record will look on paper"
    },
    {
      "start": 1035.64,
      "end": 1036.56,
      "text": "than anything else."
    },
    {
      "start": 1037.42,
      "end": 1039.2,
      "text": "He'd rather drop a doubtful case than",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1039.232,
      "end": 1040.96,
      "text": "try it and have it go against him."
    },
    {
      "start": 1041.28,
      "end": 1043.3,
      "text": "I don't know that he ever deliberately"
    },
    {
      "start": 1043.3,
      "end": 1045.34,
      "text": "framed anybody he believed innocent,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1046.02,
      "end": 1046.8,
      "text": "but I can't imagine",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1046.8,
      "end": 1049.38,
      "text": "him letting himself believe them innocent if he"
    },
    {
      "start": 1049.38,
      "end": 1051.92,
      "text": "could scrape up or twist into shape proof of their"
    },
    {
      "start": 1052.0,
      "end": 1052.18,
      "text": "guilt."
    },
    {
      "start": 1053.1,
      "end": 1054.76,
      "text": "To be sure of convicting one man,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1054.96,
      "end": 1058.22,
      "text": "he'll let half a dozen equally guilty accomplices go free,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1058.68,
      "end": 1061.36,
      "text": "if trying to convict them all might confuse his case."
    },
    {
      "start": 1062.368,
      "end": 1063.88,
      "text": "That's the choice we'll give him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1064.2,
      "end": 1065.34,
      "text": "and he'll gobble it up."
    },
    {
      "start": 1065.71,
      "end": 1067.94,
      "text": "He wouldn't want to know about the falcon."
    },
    {
      "start": 1068.94,
      "end": 1070.12,
      "text": "He'll be tickled pink to",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1070.2,
      "end": 1072.56,
      "text": "persuade himself that anything the punk tells him"
    },
    {
      "start": 1072.56,
      "end": 1075.4,
      "text": "about it is a lot of chewing gum and attempt to"
    },
    {
      "start": 1075.56,
      "end": 1076.24,
      "text": "muddle things up."
    },
    {
      "start": 1077.1,
      "end": 1078.02,
      "text": "Leave that in to me.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1079.0,
      "end": 1081.74,
      "text": "I can show him that if he starts fooling around trying to",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1081.82,
      "end": 1082.58,
      "text": "gather up everybody,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1082.89,
      "end": 1085.16,
      "text": "he's going to have a tangled case that"
    },
    {
      "start": 1085.16,
      "end": 1087.04,
      "text": "no jury will be able to make heads or"
    },
    {
      "start": 1087.08,
      "end": 1087.54,
      "text": "tails of,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1087.64,
      "end": 1089.26,
      "text": "while if he sticks to the punk,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1089.4,
      "end": 1091.76,
      "text": "he can get a conviction standing on his head."
    },
    {
      "start": 1092.27,
      "end": 1094.98,
      "text": "Gutman wagged his head sideways in a slow,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1095.06,
      "end": 1097.3,
      "text": "smiling gesture of benign disapproval."
    },
    {
      "start": 1097.44,
      "end": 1097.54,
      "text": "No,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1098.14,
      "end": 1098.36,
      "text": "sir,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1098.48,
      "end": 1098.86,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 1099.02,
      "end": 1100.38,
      "text": "I'm afraid that won't do."
    },
    {
      "start": 1100.54,
      "end": 1101.56,
      "text": "Won't do at all."
    },
    {
      "start": 1101.88,
      "end": 1103.74,
      "text": "I don't see how even this"
    },
    {
      "start": 1103.8,
      "end": 1106.0,
      "text": "district attorney of yours can link Thursby and"
    },
    {
      "start": 1106.0,
      "end": 1108.58,
      "text": "Jacoby and Wilmer together without having to."
    },
    {
      "start": 1109.54,
      "end": 1110.88,
      "text": "You don't know district attorneys,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1111.08,
      "end": 1111.78,
      "text": "Spade told him."
    },
    {
      "start": 1112.22,
      "end": 1113.68,
      "text": "The Thursby angle is easy."
    },
    {
      "start": 1113.86,
      "end": 1115.04,
      "text": "He was a gunman"
    },
    {
      "start": 1115.04,
      "end": 1115.86,
      "text": "in Sojourn Punk."
    },
    {
      "start": 1116.608,
      "end": 1118.32,
      "text": "Brian's already got a theory about that.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1118.48,
      "end": 1120.0,
      "text": "There'll be no catch there."
    },
    {
      "start": 1120.26,
      "end": 1120.36,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1121.1,
      "end": 1121.3,
      "text": "Christ,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1121.62,
      "end": 1123.32,
      "text": "they can only hang the punk once."
    },
    {
      "start": 1123.98,
      "end": 1126.72,
      "text": "Why try him for Jacoby's murder after he's been convicted",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1126.72,
      "end": 1127.58,
      "text": "of Thursby's?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1127.76,
      "end": 1130.16,
      "text": "They simply close the record by writing"
    },
    {
      "start": 1130.16,
      "end": 1131.88,
      "text": "it up against him and let it go at that."
    },
    {
      "start": 1132.42,
      "end": 1132.76,
      "text": "If,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1132.88,
      "end": 1134.16,
      "text": "as is likely enough,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1134.42,
      "end": 1135.98,
      "text": "he used the same gun on both,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1136.16,
      "end": 1137.56,
      "text": "the bullets will match up."
    },
    {
      "start": 1138.208,
      "end": 1138.8,
      "text": "Everybody will",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1138.8,
      "end": 1139.44,
      "text": "be satisfied."
    },
    {
      "start": 1139.88,
      "end": 1139.98,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1140.88,
      "end": 1141.12,
      "text": "but,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1141.48,
      "end": 1143.98,
      "text": "Gutman began and stopped to look at the boy."
    },
    {
      "start": 1144.86,
      "end": 1145.82,
      "text": "The boy advanced from the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1145.86,
      "end": 1146.12,
      "text": "doorway,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1146.28,
      "end": 1148.14,
      "text": "walking stiff-legged with his legs apart"
    },
    {
      "start": 1148.14,
      "end": 1150.32,
      "text": "until he was between Gutman and Cairo,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1150.6,
      "end": 1152.12,
      "text": "almost in the center of the floor."
    },
    {
      "start": 1152.36,
      "end": 1153.68,
      "text": "He halted there,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1153.86,
      "end": 1155.8,
      "text": "leaning forward slightly from the waist,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1156.08,
      "end": 1158.02,
      "text": "his shoulders raised towards the front."
    },
    {
      "start": 1158.62,
      "end": 1161.14,
      "text": "The pistol in his hand still hung at his side,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1161.46,
      "end": 1163.46,
      "text": "but his knuckles were white over its grip."
    },
    {
      "start": 1164.38,
      "end": 1166.72,
      "text": "His other hand was a small hard fist down at his",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1166.8,
      "end": 1167.36,
      "text": "other side."
    },
    {
      "start": 1168.32,
      "end": 1170.8,
      "text": "The indelible youngness of his face gave",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1170.8,
      "end": 1173.58,
      "text": "an indescribably vicious and inhuman turn"
    },
    {
      "start": 1173.76,
      "end": 1177.58,
      "text": "to the white-hot hatred and the cold-white malevolence in his face."
    },
    {
      "start": 1178.1,
      "end": 1179.0,
      "text": "He said to Spade in"
    },
    {
      "start": 1179.1,
      "end": 1180.26,
      "text": "a voice cramped by passion."
    },
    {
      "start": 1181.1,
      "end": 1181.7,
      "text": "You bastard,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1182.34,
      "end": 1184.38,
      "text": "get up on your feet and go for your heater.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1185.536,
      "end": 1186.66,
      "text": "Spade smiled at the boy.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1187.56,
      "end": 1188.82,
      "text": "His smile was not broad,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1189.0,
      "end": 1191.28,
      "text": "but the amusement in it seemed genuine and"
    },
    {
      "start": 1191.58,
      "end": 1192.08,
      "text": "unalloyed."
    },
    {
      "start": 1192.92,
      "end": 1193.46,
      "text": "The boy said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1193.72,
      "end": 1194.66,
      "text": "you bastard,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1194.88,
      "end": 1197.3,
      "text": "get up and shoot it out if you've got the guts."
    },
    {
      "start": 1198.3,
      "end": 1200.8,
      "text": "I've taken all the writing from you I'm going to take.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1201.04,
      "end": 1203.86,
      "text": "The amusement in Spade's smile deepened."
    },
    {
      "start": 1203.98,
      "end": 1205.74,
      "text": "He looked at Gutman and said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1206.46,
      "end": 1207.32,
      "text": "Young Wild West.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1207.88,
      "end": 1209.7,
      "text": "His voice matched his smile.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1210.72,
      "end": 1212.54,
      "text": "Maybe you ought to tell him that shooting me",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1212.6,
      "end": 1214.22,
      "text": "before you get your hands on the falcon"
    },
    {
      "start": 1214.4,
      "end": 1215.74,
      "text": "would be bad for business."
    },
    {
      "start": 1216.896,
      "end": 1219.08,
      "text": "Gutman's attempt at a smile was not successful,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1219.82,
      "end": 1222.54,
      "text": "but he kept the resultant grimace on his mottled face.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1223.52,
      "end": 1225.48,
      "text": "He licked dry lips with a dry tongue.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1226.56,
      "end": 1228.22,
      "text": "His voice was too hoarse and gritty",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1228.3,
      "end": 1231.1,
      "text": "for the paternally admonishing tone it tried to achieve."
    }
  ]
}